Edition:
Quote: It [Hooligan] at first typified a cross between a London rough and a Cockney tough, which are two terms for two but slightly different things, which have only the semblance of a shade of ashadow of difference, and are both akin to our Australasian larrikin. A larrikin is not necessarily a loafer or a criminal, though he is often, if not invariably, a member of a push which may, and usually does, contain a certain criminal element, and a still larger element verging towards criminality.
